<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ881026-0052 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief -- Forstmann andamp; Co.: Investment Firm Discussing Boosting Stake in Company </HL><SO> </SO><CO> FST </CO><IN> TNM </IN><TEXT>   General Investments America Inc. said it is in talks with Chargeurs S.A., a French firm, in connection with a &quot;possible joint submission of a proposal to acquire additional shares&quot; of Forstmann andamp; Co.    In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission, General Investments, a Los Angeles investment firm which is a unit of General Investments Group of Sydney, Australia, said no agreement with Chargeurs has been reached and no assurance can be given that one will be.    Forstmann previously said it had formed a special committee to consider, among other things, a possible sale of the company. The filing indicated that among the committee's members are Forstmann's principal holders, including General Investments, which has a 23.9% stake in the company. Chargeurs currently holds no Forstmann shares, the filing said.    Officials of Forstmann, based in Dublin, Ga., were unavailable to comment. </TEXT></DOC>